I’ll stop here as I’m forgetting my initial point, just that stigmas about mental illness being perpetuated from blockbuster movies is not okay and it causes further pain to an already struggling community. #SplitMovieHurts
The main hardships a person with DID deals with daily are PTSD, depression and memory related symptoms and these can be absolutely debilitating. Serial killing isn’t a factor.

The point of DID is functional survival, that includes blending in as much as possible and so from the outside most DID systems wouldn’t be noticeable, in fact the disorder often remains hidden for decades even from the person experiencing it.

DID is a dissociative disorder that stems from ongoing early childhood trauma. It’s a coping mechanism that initially allows the child to seperate (dissociate) from traumatic experiences to function. Different self states form with different memories, experiences & opinions form
Unfortunately, the dramatic performance & inaccuracies in the portrayal of DID in Split has caused harm to people with the disorder by perpetuating existing stigma.
In reality, people with severe and persistent mental health issues are far more likely to be the victims of violence than to perpetrate it.

Because DID has minimal accurate representation in mainstream media, a large proportion of movies with DID characters are shown to be downright dangerous. Schizophrenia tends to have a similar misrepresentation with a disproportionate number of characters portrayed as violent...

BUT Mental illness is extremely misunderstood by the general public at the best of times. When many people are getting mental health information from mostly fictional stories, they aren’t always able to differentiate between what’s based on fact & what’s sensationalised for views

I mean we as humans like supernatural/superhero movies that have a glimmer of ‘possibility’ to them and so it’s an interesting & terrifying storyline when someone who has DID could potentially have an evil alter who is secretly torturing & murderering people & not even know it..

Okay, I’ll bite... Regarding Split. It’s certainly not the 1st movie featuring a lead with DID to play the ‘evil alter’ card and I’m sure it won’t be the last. From a captivating storyline perspective then of course it’s going to be a popular film...
